From: Justin Suess <utilityemal77@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 16:17:47 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 13/14] arm64: dts: allwinner: a523: add the IOMMU and
 translate the DE

Add the A523 IOMMU node - the same H616-family block, at 0x2010000 -
and put the display engine behind it: the whole DE is master 5 in the
vendor micro-TLB map. Scanout buffers then come from dma-iommu instead
of having to land inside the low-DRAM window the DE's fetch aperture
can reach in bypass mode, which is what makes 4K framebuffers
possible.

diff --speed-large-files --no-dereference --minimal -Naur linux-7.1.3/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-a523.dtsi linux-7.1.3/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-a523.dtsi
--- linux-7.1.3/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-a523.dtsi	2026-07-06 17:31:36.424186234 +0200
+++ linux-7.1.3/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-a523.dtsi	2026-07-06 17:07:04.196057464 +0200
@@ -192,6 +192,8 @@
 				clock-names = "bus", "mod";
 				resets = <&display_clocks RST_MIXER0>;
 				power-domains = <&pck600 PD_DE>;
+				/* Vendor micro-TLB map: the whole DE is master 5 */
+				iommus = <&iommu 5>;
 
 				ports {
 					#address-cells = <1>;
@@ -578,6 +580,16 @@
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
+		iommu: iommu@2010000 {
+				compatible = "allwinner,sun55i-a523-iommu",
+				"allwinner,sun50i-h616-iommu";
+				reg = <0x02010000 0x1000>;
+				interrupts = <GIC_SPI 65 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
+				clocks = <&ccu CLK_BUS_IOMMU>;
+				resets = <&ccu RST_BUS_IOMMU>;
+				#iommu-cells = <1>;
+		};
+
 		wdt: watchdog@2050000 {
 			compatible = "allwinner,sun55i-a523-wdt";
 			reg = <0x2050000 0x20>;
